Hong Kong cook jailed for killing amorous boss . A Chinese dimsum cook was jailed for life by a Hong Kong court for killing his boss and carving up her body after claiming she had become too amorous , a newspaper said on Friday . The chef , Zeng Liang - xin from mainland China , screamed for mercy as a judge sentenced him to life imprisonment on Thursday , the South China Morning Post said . Zeng had told the court he accidently killed Wong Miu - kuen , the 37 - year - old manager of the restaurant in which he worked , after she offered him money for sex . Wong died when her head bashed a bunk bed after she was shoved to the floor , Zeng said . He admitted stealing the woman ' s jewels as he hacked off her head and chopped her up in an attempt to conceal her death . 
